Overview and Identity
Aram Towers is a landmark mixed-use development in Erbil, Iraqi Kurdistan, developed by Berev Hiviya Construction. Branded as "The Paramount of Erbil," the project positions itself as a paradigm shift in residential and commercial standards for both Kurdistan Region and Iraq as a whole. The name "Aram" carries deep cultural resonance — in Kurdish, it evokes peace, calm, and harmony — and this ethos is woven throughout the design philosophy, from natural light and open views to spaces intended to nurture both family life and professional ambition. The project has won three awards at the Arabian Property Awards 2025–2026 (in association with International Property & Travel), specifically in the categories of Mixed-Use Development, Office Development, and Residential High-Rise Development for Iraq.
Scale and Composition
The development consists of seven towers in total: five residential towers and two business (office) towers. Each residential tower rises 30 floors, while the two business towers are 18 floors each. Across the residential component, there are approximately 700 luxury family units ranging from 1-bedroom+1 (1+1) configurations up to 4-bedroom+1 (4+1) apartments and penthouses. The project provides 1,400 car parking spaces, sits on a total area of 32,000 m², and includes 14,000 m² of landscaped gardens and green spaces. It is described as the only compound in Iraq with more than 40 amenities.
Location
Aram Towers is situated at what the brochure calls "the new heart of Erbil," surrounded by the city's most prominent luxury residential and commercial projects. The site sits near the junction of major roads including the 150m Street, 120m Street, and 100m Street, with the Ainkawa neighborhood on two sides, and direct adjacency to Erbil Avenue and the Erbil Hills Golf Course. The project faces panoramic views of what is described as Kurdistan Region's and Iraq's only golf course. In terms of proximity, Erbil International Airport is just 5 minutes away, Family Mall is 8 minutes, Divan Erbil Hotel is 9 minutes, Sami Abdulrahman Park and PAR Hospital are both 10 minutes away, and the UNESCO-listed Erbil Citadel is 11 minutes away.
Residential Towers — Unit Types and Floor Plans
The residential towers are divided into two architectural typologies — Type A and Type B — each with mirror variants to optimize views and orientation relative to the site's surroundings.
Type A towers (Towers A and B) offer five unit configurations. The 1+1 A unit has a gross area of 152.67 m² and includes a combined living room and kitchen of 39.87 m², a master bedroom of 18.82 m², a master bathroom of 4.41 m², a hall of 4.49 m², a WC of 2.25 m², a laundry room of 0.91 m², and a balcony of 26.38 m². The 2+1 A unit is 170.25 m² gross, with a living room of 31.16 m², a kitchen of 16.16 m², two bedrooms, two bathrooms, a hall, and a balcony of 10.90 m². The 2+1 B variant is 172.29 m² gross and similarly configured with slight dimensional differences. The 3+1 A unit has a gross area of 280.78 m² featuring a living room of 50.55 m², a kitchen of 12.40 m², two standard bedrooms, two master bedrooms, two bathrooms, a laundry room, and a large balcony of 41.69 m². The largest in Type A, the 4+1 A unit is 344.92 m² gross, including a living room of 38.77 m², kitchen of 18.42 m², a dressing room of 4.48 m², two master bedrooms (34.97 m² and 6.34 m²), two standard bedrooms, an office room of 15.88 m², laundry, multiple bathrooms, and a balcony of 29.89 m².
Type B towers (Towers C and E) offer a different set of configurations suited to a slightly different footprint. The smallest is the 1+1 B at 107.91 m² gross, with a combined living room and kitchen of 34.51 m², master bedroom of 16.73 m², master bathroom of 3.66 m², WC of 3.27 m², and balcony of 10.92 m². The 2+1 E is 193.88 m² gross, featuring a living room of 27.72 m², kitchen of 11.25 m², one bedroom of 14.05 m², master bedroom of 18.52 m², two bathrooms, and a notably generous balcony of 30.11 m². The 2+1 D is 234.15 m² and includes a living room of 48.61 m², bedroom, master bedroom of 22.29 m², and a substantial balcony of 37.97 m². The 3+1 D unit at 240.50 m² gross includes a living room of 27.22 m², two standard bedrooms, a master bedroom with dressing room (25.11 m² + 7.11 m²), a master bathroom, laundry room, and balcony of 11.29 m². The most expansive Type B residential option is the 3+2 E at 340.39 m² gross — a large configuration featuring a living room of 38.23 m², a separate dining room of 14.08 m², two standard bedrooms with dressing rooms, a master bedroom of 27.96 m² with its own dressing room (9.22 m²) and master bathroom, laundry room, WC, and a balcony of 28.38 m².
Tower D is also a Type A layout and Tower C and Tower E use the Type B layout, as indicated by the orientation circles showing each tower's position and view direction on the site plan.
Office Towers (BT1 and BT2)
The two business towers — BT1 and BT2 — share identical floor plate configurations, each offering six distinct office unit types per floor. Office 1 is the second-largest at 198.67 m², and Office 2 is 108.94 m². Office 3 is 108.02 m², Office 4 is 99.92 m², Office 5 is the largest at 259.85 m², and Office 6 is 143.53 m². All office units are designed with floor-to-ceiling glass facing the adjacent Erbil Hills Golf Course, offering unobstructed panoramic views. The offices are described as fully equipped premium spaces, designed to maximize natural light and inspire productivity while maintaining a luxury aesthetic.
Amenities — More Than 40 in Total
Aram Towers is marketed as the only compound in Iraq to offer more than 40 amenities. These include lavish entrances with grand lobbies, integrated smart home technology in all units, clean balconies with no external split air conditioning units, a 360° rooftop dining experience, bathrooms with luxury finishes, eco-friendly electric vehicle charging points, free Wi-Fi across all outdoor zones, family-only units (1–4 bedrooms, no studio apartments), an indoor infinity swimming pool with views, high thermal and sound insulation throughout, dedicated business towers and lounges, extensive green spaces and landscaped gardens, panoramic views of the Erbil skyline, and 24/7 concierge and maintenance services.
Further amenities listed include: a running track, a spa, pet-friendly spaces, outdoor play areas for children, an outdoor gym, a cycling track, an indoor gym, a multipurpose hall, a rooftop lounge restaurant, a children's play area, a lawn with seating areas, a business lounge, a central vacuum system, a nursery and kindergarten, a panoramic viewing area, central LPG gas infrastructure, 3-meter-high ceilings throughout, and an infinity pool.
Residential Entrances
Each residential tower block has its own entrance hub, which goes well beyond a standard lobby. These functional entrances include a spacious waiting area, a fully equipped business center, a children's playroom, a multipurpose events space, a post room, a store, and additional convenient facilities. The entrance floor plan for Tower B, for example, shows a clearly delineated business center and post room of approximately 12.2 m².
Interior Design and Finishes
All living spaces and bedrooms feature premium fittings sourced from international luxury brands. Kitchens are designed with high-end cabinetry, modern metal profiles, and mood lighting. Bathrooms are finished with luxurious wallpaper-effect materials, designer fixtures, and accent lighting. The brochure describes the interiors as a "fabric of sophistication and elegance," with every room — from the living areas to the master bedroom — finished to the highest standard. The apartments offer panoramic views of either the golf course or the city skyline, described as a unique architectural concept ensuring seamless transitions between communal and private spaces within the residence.
The Penthouse Experience
Aram Towers' topmost levels include penthouses described as "the crown of Aram Towers." These penthouse units are positioned above the golf course, offering what the brochure calls a rare perspective — sunrise views, infinity pools that visually blend into the cityscape below, curved architectural lines, bold design, and floor-to-ceiling glass. The penthouse concept is presented as a reimagining of urban luxury living.
Philosophy and Brand Values
The project's marketing philosophy is built around six core experiential values: "Feel the Warmth" (effortless sophistication and tailored comfort), "Reunited with Family" (a community where business and living are thoughtfully separated yet seamlessly connected), "Begins with Love" (growth measured not in square meters but in moments), "Taste the World" (global brands and fine dining in one iconic destination), "Elevate Your Spirit" (personal renewal beginning at home), and "Breathe Deeper" (a rare harmony between architecture and nature with open skies and quiet luxury). The development explicitly positions itself as not just towers, but a whole community.
Developer Track Record
Before launching Aram Towers, the developer Berev Hiviya Construction had already successfully delivered two earlier projects: Aram Village 1 and Davos Village, both in Erbil. Together these comprise more than 1,500 residential units within fully serviced gated communities. These prior projects are cited as establishing the developer's reputation for well-planned neighborhood design and are presented as the foundation for the more ambitious Aram Towers vision.
Awards
The project won three Arabian Property Awards for 2025–2026, which are among the most prestigious real estate accolades in the region. The three winning categories were Mixed-Use Development (Iraq), Office Development (Iraq), and Residential High-Rise Development (Iraq), all awarded in association with International Property & Travel magazine.
